info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued March 11 at 4:39PM CST until March 13 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 AM CDT MONDAY... * WHAT...Heavy snow. Additional snow accumulations of 3 to 8 inches, except 8 to 13 inches for the higher terrain of the North Shore. * WHERE...In Minnesota, North St. Louis, Central St. Louis, Northern Aitkin, South Aitkin and Pine Counties. In Wisconsin, Douglas County. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Mille Lacs Band, Big Sandy Lake, East Lake, Hinckley and, Lena Lake areas and the Bois Forte Band, Lake Vermilion and, Nett Lake areas. * WHEN...Until 1 AM CDT Monday. * IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.
